abstract: What arguments over the movie series say about our nation.
snippet: What arguments over the movie series say about our nation.
lead_paragraph: Like a lot of Americans, I have formative memories of my first exposure to George Lucas’s epic tale of space Rebels defeating a planet-destroying Empire. I got so excited as a little kid in 1977 about seeing “Star Wars: A New Hope” that I threw up outside the theater.

abstract: Like climate change, the aging of America demands a serious rethinking of the way we live.
snippet: Like climate change, the aging of America demands a serious rethinking of the way we live.
lead_paragraph: One of the paradoxes of this presidential campaign is that while many of the candidates are in their eighth decade of life, fundamental issues associated with the aging of American society are still receiving relatively little attention from the public, the press and politicians themselves. In 2031, the oldest baby boomers will turn 85, entering the land of the “old old” and facing exponentially higher risk for dementia, serious physical disabilities and long-term dependency.
